			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">function GetAunoBio&#40;$name, $rk_num&#41; 
<br />
&#123;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$socket = fsockopen&#40;&quot;auno.org&quot;, 80, &amp;$errornumber, &amp;$errorrstring,4&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;stream_set_timeout&#40;$socket, 4&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;if &#40;!$socket&#41; return &quot;&#91;socket failed to open, &#91;$errornumber&#93;$errorrstring&#93;\n&quot;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;fputs&#40;$socket, &quot;GET /ao/char.php?t=auno-print&amp;dimension=$rk_num&amp;name=$name&amp;cmd=search HTTP/1.0\nHost&#58; auno.org\n\n&quot;&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;while &#40;!feof&#40;$socket&#41; &amp;&amp; substr&#40;$result,-3&#41;!=&quot;0\r\n&quot;&#41; 
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $result.= fgets&#40;$socket, 4096&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;return $result;
<br />
&#125;
<br />
$rawHTMLresult = GetAunoBio&#40;&quot;Deng&quot;,2&#41;;
<br />
echo $rawHTMLresult;
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
ok, I think the problem was that I needed to send the <span style="font-weight: bold">Host</span> variable in the header.
<br />

<br />
so hopefully, the <span style="font-weight: bold">stream_set_timeout()</span> will get respected and timeout after 4 seconds (which is plenty of time).<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold"> </span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
